  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UK Met Office Assessment of Weather &amp; Climate Hazard Impacts in Sub Saharan Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim is to gather evidence on the existing actions taken across sectors in response to weather and climate hazards in Sub-Saharan Africa. This should highlight obvious gaps in the provision of services to mitigate weather and climate hazards. Provide an overview of how responses to weather and climate hazards in the region are triggered and how they are resourced and financed.

Largely desk-based with KIIs and regular interaction with UKMO.</narrative>
  </description>
